1
00:00:01,070 --> 00:00:02,870
So, another project.

2
00:00:03,330 --> 00:00:09,370
We're building an electric lift to replace the ladder up to the second floor.

3
00:00:10,430 --> 00:00:11,990
The ladder won't fit.

4
00:00:12,530 --> 00:00:14,350
By the client's requirements.

5
00:00:15,410 --> 00:00:19,490
The spot where it needs to fit is this platform here.

6
00:00:21,770 --> 00:00:26,630
The dimensions where it needs to fit are...

7
00:00:26,630 --> 00:00:31,550
1 meter by 68 cm.

8
00:00:31,970 --> 00:00:35,590
The platform is 65 cm.

9
00:00:36,890 --> 00:00:40,770
The whole dimension to the railing is 68 cm.

10
00:00:41,490 --> 00:00:42,710
Previous step.

11
00:00:43,650 --> 00:00:45,570
So what are we putting this together from?

12
00:00:46,730 --> 00:00:53,670
The main element of the build is this kind of device.

13
00:00:53,870 --> 00:00:55,070
Called a chain hoist.

14
00:00:55,910 --> 00:00:57,650
For lifting loads.

15
00:00:58,510 --> 00:01:02,850
Its lift capacity is about 600 kg.

16
00:01:03,090 --> 00:01:04,590
Probably pulls more than that.

17
00:01:06,030 --> 00:01:15,910
For the build I picked up a metal plate — 10 mm sheet iron.

18
00:01:17,850 --> 00:01:23,310
Then we got some angle iron.

19
00:01:24,530 --> 00:01:25,910
63 angle.

20
00:01:28,910 --> 00:01:29,350
Roller.

21
00:01:31,490 --> 00:01:38,790
And this set of bearing-mounted rollers with a plastic shell.

22
00:01:40,090 --> 00:01:46,110
Moving on to drawing the supports for the platform.

23
00:01:47,050 --> 00:01:51,070
We need to place these rollers.

24
00:01:52,650 --> 00:01:57,150
The angle guide will roll between them.

25
00:02:00,390 --> 00:02:07,450
The support itself will sit on this plane we drew.

26
00:02:08,810 --> 00:02:10,810
This is how it'll look.

27
00:02:10,930 --> 00:02:12,370
It'll be on top.

28
00:02:12,650 --> 00:02:15,950
The platform itself, where the person will stand.

29
00:02:19,730 --> 00:02:23,990
The roller guide has this profile.

30
00:02:25,370 --> 00:02:26,850
This is how it's welded up.

31
00:02:28,150 --> 00:02:29,370
Out of two angles.

32
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:33,190
The length can be anything.

33
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:42,910
In this case, from the bottom of the platform to the top of the floor is 2.80 m.

34
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:49,650
If you want, you can do it for 6 meters of travel.

35
00:02:50,330 --> 00:02:53,410
You'd just need to weld these spacers in the middle.

36
00:02:54,510 --> 00:02:57,730
This part is the wall mount.

37
00:02:58,950 --> 00:03:00,370
Holes will be drilled here.

38
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:03,310
And mounted with anchor bolts.

39
00:03:05,030 --> 00:03:10,370
This is the platform the motor with the traction mechanism attaches to.

40
00:03:12,130 --> 00:03:13,850
Welded to the end.

41
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:20,860
A small cutout was made in the platform here.

42
00:03:21,390 --> 00:03:25,050
A baseboard runs through here, per the build.

43
00:03:25,810 --> 00:03:28,390
The baseboard isn't plastic, it's ceramic.

44
00:03:28,390 --> 00:03:31,630
So we had to do this cutout.

45
00:03:34,470 --> 00:03:38,730
Now we'll cut supports for the platform.

46
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:41,590
And mount them here.

47
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:45,510
Next we'll show how this whole thing rolls.

48
00:03:47,170 --> 00:03:49,790
And we need to design a control circuit.

49
00:03:50,930 --> 00:03:55,750
There's an emergency stop button on this one.

50
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:59,070
And a button for down-up movement.

51
00:04:00,230 --> 00:04:02,490
We'll apply this in the build.

52
00:04:02,650 --> 00:04:09,830
We also need a call button so we can summon the lift down if it's at the top.

53
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,450
We'll add that separately.

54
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:21,070
And also install extra power cutoffs in the form of limit switches.

55
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:28,170
When the platform with the person on it reaches the top, the lift should shut off.

56
00:04:28,350 --> 00:04:33,390
And likewise on the way down, the lift should automatically shut off too.

57
00:04:35,110 --> 00:04:36,310
Here's one.

58
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:39,830
And the second.

59
00:04:40,170 --> 00:04:42,890
Now we're marking where the rollers go.

60
00:04:43,930 --> 00:04:45,370
Starting with the two rear ones.

61
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:50,970
Drawing a right angle with a square.

62
00:04:52,530 --> 00:05:01,490
A spot where the platform surface is perpendicular to the drilling, with a center punch or dowel nail.

63
00:05:02,890 --> 00:05:08,230
Next it'll be drilled with a thin pilot bit.

64
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:14,190
And then drilled out to size.

65
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:17,210
Bolt thread.

66
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:22,010
Here's what it looks like in the workpiece.

67
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:26,530
And here's how it comes out with the rollers.

68
00:05:26,810 --> 00:05:30,110
Two on one side, the third from this side.

69
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:37,330
So our workpiece can now freely slide along the angle guide.

70
00:05:37,630 --> 00:05:39,770
Our build is mounted.

71
00:05:41,010 --> 00:05:43,530
So they roll for us.

72
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:46,330
Like this.

73
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:55,290
We're going to mount the platform on this surface now.

74
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:05,450
Platform installed.

75
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:08,910
So what were we doing here?

76
00:06:09,490 --> 00:06:20,870
We were making these cutouts so the platform sits per our requirements — 68 cm from the wall to the edge of the platform.

77
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:22,390
Held the distance.

78
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:28,890
We tack-welded the guide with rollers in place.

79
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:33,850
Tacks visible from all sides.

80
00:06:35,450 --> 00:06:40,670
Now we'll take the platform off and do the permanent welds.

81
00:06:41,870 --> 00:06:44,730
We need to remove the rollers so they don't get burned.

82
00:06:45,590 --> 00:06:47,570
Here's one interesting detail.

83
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:52,050
You can see the edge of the roller sticks out beyond the iron.

84
00:06:52,750 --> 00:07:01,530
That's done so when the platform comes down, it lands softly on the lower iron and there's no clanging impact.

85
00:07:02,930 --> 00:07:04,950
That's how it all looks.

86
00:07:05,350 --> 00:07:08,650
And now a test run.

87
00:07:09,810 --> 00:07:13,130
For now we just hooked the hook to the center.

88
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:15,770
Let's see how it goes.

89
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,550
Off we go.

90
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:23,870
Here's how it'll roll.

91
00:07:25,450 --> 00:07:27,230
This is how it moves.

92
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,600
The platform moves.

93
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:38,540
We still need to install something here on the inside.

94
00:07:38,820 --> 00:07:45,140
Spacer rollers in this part, so it doesn't shift axially.

95
00:07:47,220 --> 00:07:50,500
It'll rest against this part and this one.

96
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:55,440
Interesting build.

97
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:07,470
Platform installed, partially painted.

98
00:08:09,090 --> 00:08:14,330
The platform now rolls freely on the rollers.

99
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:18,750
This is how it goes.

100
00:08:20,210 --> 00:08:21,970
You can move it.

101
00:08:22,050 --> 00:08:23,930
You can see the rollers working.

102
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:28,390
Welded an eye for attaching the cable.

103
00:08:30,890 --> 00:08:36,270
Here's what the spacer rollers on the inside look like.

104
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:41,150
They ride on the inner surfaces here and here.

105
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:43,470
So, next.

106
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:48,590
Now we made some improvements to the rollers we bought.

107
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:50,770
Added a washer.

108
00:08:51,650 --> 00:08:53,450
All of this on bolts.

109
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:58,110
And the bolts with glue, so the plastic doesn't wiggle.

110
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:00,250
Now it's solidly fixed.

111
00:09:00,930 --> 00:09:02,450
Two bearings here.

112
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:10,730
A machinist cut a groove originally, so the plastic doesn't slip sideways.

113
00:09:12,330 --> 00:09:16,450
And we also improved two of the rollers.

114
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:21,170
Welded some heavy-duty retaining washers.

115
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:26,450
These are the rollers that go in this spacer area.

116
00:09:27,430 --> 00:09:30,450
You can see the oval-shaped hole.

117
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:40,810
The bolt goes into this hole.

118
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:47,990
And so it can move, pressing the roller down.

119
00:09:48,450 --> 00:09:55,270
That's how we adjust how tightly the platform is held against wobble.

120
00:09:55,270 --> 00:10:07,030
And we also need this later — if the plastic wears slightly over time, we can lift the roller a bit like this and press it harder.

121
00:10:08,390 --> 00:10:19,350
For holes like these, we need a wider support, so a washer was welded on with a MIG welder.

122
00:10:20,350 --> 00:10:27,810
For the rollers — for these nuts — we got copper washers.

123
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:38,750
Copper is a soft metal, so when the nut tightens it grips well and the nut can't back off.

124
00:10:41,410 --> 00:10:43,730
Little tricks like that.

125
00:10:44,130 --> 00:11:00,290
A cutout was made here so that as the cable winds onto the drum, it can move back and forth on the drum.

126
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:06,890
So we have to make sure it doesn't rub against the platform — it has to move like this.

127
00:11:08,090 --> 00:11:12,730
Rollers installed — only the main retainers are left.

128
00:11:13,850 --> 00:11:18,290
We're making those out of metal — here's their profile.

129
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:28,590
For this, we bought a factory roller — it comes with this profile out of the box.

130
00:11:29,370 --> 00:11:33,890
Doesn't fit us — we need to bring it down to this shape.

131
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:44,570
Without going to a machinist or a milling guy or whoever does this, you can do it at home with a drill.

132
00:11:45,950 --> 00:11:52,870
Bolt it through the hole, tighten this handle, it sits like so.

133
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:59,930
Start it up, set it, and it rotates.

134
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:07,990
Take a small angle grinder, turn it on, and shave this part off.

135
00:12:08,830 --> 00:12:09,750
The excess.

136
00:12:11,010 --> 00:12:12,710
Here's how it works.

137
00:12:14,070 --> 00:12:20,910
And then bring it to shape with a file and a bit of sandpaper.

138
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:26,390
That way you can easily do various jobs at home.

139
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,690
Here's how it goes.

140
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:54,340
The roller heats up while being worked, so pour water on it periodically.

141
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:07,340
Put the second roller in for machining.

142
00:13:08,740 --> 00:13:16,340
Here's the first one — you can see the diameter of this part has been reduced too.

143
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:19,140
We don't need such a big roller.

144
00:13:19,860 --> 00:13:23,420
And here you can see the chamfer.

145
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,620
Some metal removed.

146
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:33,500
Done specifically because the guide is painted, so that this edge doesn't slice the paint and fray it.

147
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:37,500
That's why we made this small chamfer.

148
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:41,040
That's how the roller came out.

149
00:13:41,980 --> 00:13:46,640
Now we'll machine this surface the same way.

150
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:53,020
Now you can see how it goes on the lift.

151
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,040
Here's the hole.

152
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:57,340
Here it goes in.

153
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,660
Just need to mount it on the guide.

154
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:05,080
And this roller will engage here.

155
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:08,260
It fits well here.

156
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:17,720
We tried using the soft-surfaced rollers in this spot.

157
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:25,440
But they turned out not to be a good fit because this is the highest-loaded spot.

158
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:32,480
It carries the full support of the platform and all the weight applied to the lift.

159
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:37,480
So we decided to swap to these metal ones.

160
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,680
Better suited.

161
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:44,200
And in other places, those soft rollers work great.

162
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,000
Rubber doesn't deform.

163
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,000
Works really well.

164
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,500
We've already ridden on it.

165
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:59,340
Pulls great — this build can lift even two people.

166
00:15:02,380 --> 00:15:05,840
But it needs a little fine-tuning.

167
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:09,720
Here's the build that came out.

168
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:12,540
Looks like this.

169
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:18,420
There's a roller — it'll also be covered up so fingers can't get in there.

170
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:24,740
And here it travels vertically.

171
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:43,300
Working from the system up, went to max.

172
00:15:59,340 --> 00:16:01,840
Now we'll get on it.

173
00:16:03,740 --> 00:16:04,600
Let's go.

174
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:14,880
As you can see, lifts me with no problem.

175
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:20,540
I'm almost 100 kg — not small.

176
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:29,000
We tried riding two-up — it pulls both of us.

177
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:31,720
But the motor strains, of course.

178
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,940
For one person it's just right.

179
00:16:41,980 --> 00:16:45,060
Quite a contraption.

180
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:45,980
Installed.

181
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:47,900
Our lift is installed.

182
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:56,080
Here's an interesting system in the attic that we got.

183
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,040
What did we do?

184
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:03,920
The wiring and connections kept exactly as-is.

185
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:09,140
We installed a remote in case we're lifting cargo on the lift.

186
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,720
The system also works.

187
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:16,080
You can move up and down with the button.

188
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,480
This is the backup control.

189
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:26,820
Main control is done with the buttons on the lift platform itself.

190
00:17:26,820 --> 00:17:33,260
One button moves up, another button moves down.

191
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:38,580
The lift is operated with the feet by pressing this button.

192
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:41,260
While the button is held, the platform moves.

193
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:49,520
There are end switches that cut the system the moment the platform reaches the required level.

194
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:53,500
Here it stops at this adjustable stop.

195
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:57,320
And the lift platform stops.

196
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:04,460
There's an end-of-travel cutoff below the platform too.

197
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:11,460
On the platform where the motor itself sits — using this button.

198
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:20,620
You can also see the two-button control system here.

199
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:26,680
One button is down, the other is up.

200
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:33,240
We also added a call button for convenience.

201
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:38,380
Say if a person went upstairs and the platform is in the upper position.

202
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:45,980
Then if someone else needs to go up, there's a call button to bring the lift back down.

203
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:48,800
Press it, the platform comes down.

204
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:53,280
And there's the same button up top.

205
00:18:54,340 --> 00:18:59,200
For the analogous call to bring the lift platform up.

206
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:06,340
The mechanism runs on rollers.

207
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:12,340
We showed it in detail during the build.

208
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:16,540
Here's how it looks on the wall.

209
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:22,760
Replaced the standard cable with a thicker one for reliability.

210
00:19:24,340 --> 00:19:25,900
Now we'll ride it.

211
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:27,360
Get on the platform.

212
00:19:28,820 --> 00:19:29,740
Stand.

213
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:37,620
And press the button to lift the platform up.

214
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:43,320
Hands totally free.

215
00:19:48,490 --> 00:19:55,350
Here's the breaking stop for this button, per the build.

216
00:19:55,830 --> 00:19:58,490
Here's our main mechanism.

217
00:19:59,410 --> 00:20:02,450
This is the roller the cable runs on.

218
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:12,210
And we also implemented a safety system limiting upward platform travel.

219
00:20:12,210 --> 00:20:19,150
This roller, which runs along the back wall of the guide, hits a stop.

220
00:20:19,770 --> 00:20:21,270
And can't move any further.

221
00:20:21,870 --> 00:20:25,630
And the electrical side is cut by this button.

222
00:20:26,210 --> 00:20:32,110
We also set the system up so that you can't press two buttons at the same time.

223
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:33,290
Nothing happens.

224
00:20:33,350 --> 00:20:36,770
For example, if you're moving up and press the second button.

225
00:20:36,910 --> 00:20:39,150
With two buttons pressed simultaneously, no movement.

226
00:20:40,090 --> 00:20:42,210
No contact, nothing.

227
00:20:46,970 --> 00:20:50,090
So that's the safety provision for this part.

228
00:20:53,030 --> 00:20:54,430
The opening isn't finished yet.

229
00:20:54,850 --> 00:20:58,010
But that'll be done later.

230
00:20:58,290 --> 00:20:59,350
For convenience.

231
00:21:00,210 --> 00:21:03,610
And one more thing.

232
00:21:03,970 --> 00:21:06,410
You can press the button to bring the lift down.

233
00:21:09,150 --> 00:21:12,030
And under its own weight, it descends smoothly.

234
00:21:12,190 --> 00:21:15,990
Without weight, it would jump.

235
00:21:16,990 --> 00:21:18,070
The lift brakes.

236
00:21:18,350 --> 00:21:21,930
So the lift platform stops.

237
00:21:22,710 --> 00:21:23,490
You can jump.

238
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:26,910
Also done for safety.
